  <span id="freeText13638260309351651964" style="display:none">I have to admit that I didn't read it carefully. Mostly it's a more self-helpy version of lots of pop-psych books I've been reading lately. And it's a little too general, in that it assumes most ppl are very similar to one another (even when it reports success rates of, say, 18% before &amp; 35% now).<br /><br />But it's got some terrific guidelines, mantras, examples, and actions, so if you're motivated but unsure about how to begin to make the change you want to see in your life or your team, it's worth checking out. Or maybe check out <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.switchthebook.com/resources">www.switchthebook.com/resources</a> first.</span>
